{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9f3f3e22-f8c1-4045-8b09-63daa63a33a6","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .dmp file. The best tool for this on Linux is **`dotnet-dump analyze`**. Let me check what's available in your environment:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013HzrtG1Yb6PtgqpnHg5sPk","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Checking dump analysis tools"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01P7CUZXypHvW2BdFtheFuLY","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"which dotnet-dump 2>/dev/null; which dotnet 2>/dev/null; which lldb 2>/dev/null; ls *.dmp 2>/dev/null || echo \"No .dmp files in cwd\"","description":"Check for dump analysis tools and dump files","initial_wait":10},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Check for dump analysis tools and dump files"}],"interactionId":"8552cdf3-17b9-4c70-a3c7-6d6bbde664b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this. I should look at what tools are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **configuring and collecting** crash dumps, and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So that skill is not appropriate here.\n\nThere's also a `dotnet-trace-collect` skill for capturing diagnostic artifacts, but that's for live performance issues, not post-mortem analysis.\n\n\nSince none of the available skills handle dump analysis, I'll guide them directly through the process. The best approach on Linux would be using `dotnet-dump analyze`, so I should check if that tool is available and walk them through analyzing their crash dump file.","outputTokens":590},"id":"e42bba6c-a987-4975-aeea-1a606d75ff6c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:02:04.617Z","parentId":"1a230899-7ce7-41dc-b0e4-0066551f634f"}
